Dallas investor Harold C. Simmons said he raised his stake in Lockheed Corp. to 10.43% of the common outstanding. 

In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, Mr. Simmons said he controls 6,621,900 Lockheed common shares, including 887,100 shares bought by NL Industries Inc. and NL Chemicals Inc. from Aug. 1 to last Thursday for $47.25 to $48.75 a share.
The filing said Valhi Inc. sold 272,400 shares from Aug. 30 to Sept. 26 for $48.50 to $53 a share. 

By Aug. 1, Mr. Simmons and the companies had raised their stake in Lockheed to 9.46%. 

The filing said the additional shares were bought to increase the Simmons companies' equity interests in Calabasas, Calif.-based Lockheed.
More shares may be bought or sold in the open market or in private transactions, depending on market conditions and other factors. 

